$ SAS statements: libname
@ libname

The length of a libname cannot be longer than 8 characters. A notable exception is the reserved libname → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/dictionary[`dictionary`].

The return code of the most recent `libname` statementis stored in → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros/variables/automatic/syslibrc.

{ Windows path

  gh|about-SAS|/programming/statements/libname/windows-path.sas||

}
{ (Logically) concatenated libraries

  gh|about-SAS|/programming/statements/libname/concatenated.sas||

}
{ clear

  Deallocate the library after use:
  gh|about-SAS|/programming/statements/libname/clear.sas||

}
{ Connecting to a Server

  Using the `server` option to connect to a remote host/server:
  gh|about-SAS|/programming/statements/libname/server.sas||


}
{ Automatically creating directories

  The → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options/dlcreatedir option can be used to automatically create a directory with a libname statement if the directory
  does not exist.

}

sa:

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/statements,
  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/functions/pathname

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/statements/libname/sql_functions
